The compounds were identified based on their GC retention indices on both columns and through their mass spectra. Retention indices, calculated by linear interpolation relative to the retention times of C8–C24
n-alkanes (Eq. 1)62, were compared with those of authentic products included in the Faculty of Pharmacy of the University of Coimbra laboratory database and/or literature data63,64. Acquired mass spectra were compared with reference spectra from the laboratory database, Wiley/NIST library and literature data63,65. Relative amounts of individual components were calculated based on GC raw data areas without a response factor correction for flame ionization detection.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
